<br>
That endless stream of monsters, all of which were practically immune to all magic because the encounter designers didn't want them slowed and there was no way to flag them as unslowable?  That endless stream of melee items with ever-increasing +hp and ever-better ratios, when the best gear a caster could get had, if it was really uber, Flowing Thought 1?<br>
<br>
Luclin didn't really redress that balance.  Sure, Luclin with its AA's and (later) its focus items brought better caster gear and helped to bring casters back up into line with melees, but rogues or monks were still better than wizards or mages in the damage dealer role, even at the end of Luclin.<br>
<br>
Well, in Planes of Power, the pendulum does appear to have swung the other way, and perhaps with some boss mob encounters, it has swung a little too far.  Nevertheless, personally I am delighted to see some attempt by Sony to end the long-entrenched Everquest technique of having one or two monolithic main tanks supported by an army of clerics in rotation.  The game did need a change from that.<br>
<br>
It should be desirable for all the melees on the raid to have high AC and good HP gear, not just the main tanks, and I can see that the AE rampage encounters were designed with this in mind.<br>
<br>
I also think that it's a good thing to have some encounters where melees need to use their ranged weapons in preference to their toe-to-toe ones.<br>
<br>
I fear that the encounters as implemented may have fallen short of these ideals because the AE rampage is hitting too hard on too many encounters.  But I do appreciate the thought that went into designing this content. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#2F2F4F><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub14.ezboard.com/bthesteelwarrior.showUserPublicProfile?gid=ainmer>Ainmer</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>knows that Warriors are superior</span><br>  Posts: 75<br> <font color=#FF0000>(3/21/03 8:29 am)</font><br>    <BR><img src=http://ainmer.homestead.com/files/roland.jpg WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: I dream of dancing eggplant.</span><hr size=1> <!--EZCODE QUOTE START--><blockquote><strong><em>Quote:</em></strong><hr>Nevertheless, personally I am delighted to see some attempt by Sony to end the long-entrenched Everquest technique of having one or two monolithic main tanks supported by an army of clerics in rotation. The game did need a change from that.<hr></blockquote><!--EZCODE QUOTE END--><br>
